name: 3-chloro-1h-indazole
Reason: The basic unit for this compound is indazole, which has a typical melting point of around 102°C. The chlorine (Cl) substituent has different effects: it increases molecular weight and enhances intermolecular interactions through dipole-dipole attraction and possible weak lattice integration, which typically raises the melting point by approximately +40°C. Therefore, the overall impact of the Cl group is expected to increase the melting point of the basic indazole unit.
